{
  "texts": [
    "The convolutional neural network architecture called the VGG framework, or VGGNet, that covers 16 layers is also known as VGG16.",
    "It was developed by A. Zisserman and K. Simonyan from the University of Oxford.",
    "The study article titled \"Very Deep Convolutional Networks for Large-Scale Image Recognition\" contains the framework that these authors released.",
    "In ImageNet, the VGG16 model outperforms top-5 accuracy results of about 92.7%.",
    "A resource called ImageNet has over 14 million photos that fall into about 1000 categories."
  ]
}